  "prompt": "Are there any websites like DAAD for masters in US?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several websites and resources similar to the DAAD (German Academic Exchange Service) that provide information and support for students looking to pursue a master's degree in the United States. Here are some notable ones:\n\n1. **EducationUSA**: This is a network supported by the U.S. Department of State that provides accurate and comprehensive information about studying in the United States. They have advising centers around the world and offer guidance on the application process, financial aid, and more.\n\n2. **Peterson's**: This resource offers a comprehensive database of graduate programs in the U.S., along with advice on the application process and test preparation resources.\n\n3. **GradSchools.com**: This website allows you to search for graduate programs by subject, location, and category. It also offers advice and tips on choosing programs and applying to them.\n\n4. **InternationalStudent.com**: While this site covers all levels of study, it has a section dedicated to graduate studies, including advice on how to choose a program, funding options, and visa requirements.\n\n5. **Study in the USA**: This site provides information on a wide range of programs, including master's degrees. It offers resources for understanding the application process, financial aid options, and student visas.\n\n6. **US News Graduate School Rankings**: Although primarily known for its rankings, US News provides detailed information on various graduate programs, including admission requirements and other useful insights.\n\n7. **Fulbright Program**: Though primarily a fellowship program, Fulbright provides extensive information and support for international students through its various programs and resources.\n\nThese resources can help you explore your options for graduate study in the U.S. and provide guidance throughout the application process.",
